So much for eyes.

33:42.700 --> 33:47.100
How old are you?
You brought it up. I'm curious.

33:47.300 --> 33:52.200
- Not that you're ugly.
- I can take the compliment.

33:52.400 --> 33:57.000
But my knees start knocking when
you turn on the charm full blast.

33:57.200 --> 34:00.800
What's with the dark?

34:03.200 --> 34:05.400
Dawn patrol.

34:05.600 --> 34:09.400
My son had
a full-blown attack.

34:09.500 --> 34:14.900
And for extra fun
they gave us the wrong antibiotics.

34:15.100 --> 34:17.900
No!

34:18.100 --> 34:22.199
It's bacon for the dog.

34:24.000 --> 34:28.300
Last week I was playing the piano
for him. And he likes it.

34:28.400 --> 34:34.900
So I decide
I'm going to make a little joke.

34:43.800 --> 34:48.100
It's a beautiful day for our walk.

35:00.100 --> 35:03.700
Look at that dog.

35:03.900 --> 35:08.900
I've got to give you
something real good.

35:09.400 --> 35:13.200
I'm going to show it to you.

35:14.400 --> 35:17.400
Don't be like me.

35:17.500 --> 35:23.300
Stay as you are. You're perfect.
I'll get you something to eat.

35:25.400 --> 35:28.500
I'd like to be treated like that.

35:29.900 --> 35:34.200
Let's go home and do some writing.

35:35.500 --> 35:40.200
''He had made the girl happy.
And what a girl.''

35:40.600 --> 35:44.100
''You've saved my life, she said.''

35:45.600 --> 35:49.100
''You'd better make it up to me.''

35:51.900 --> 35:57.900
Done!
Yes, I hate the doggie.

35:59.100 --> 36:02.400
62 books. Done.

36:03.100 --> 36:08.600
- We have to cut back all expenses.
- He has no medical insurance?

36:08.800 --> 36:13.800
These are the food receipts,
the household expenses.

36:14.000 --> 36:17.800
- Here's one for the dog again.
- I got it.

36:18.000 --> 36:21.000
And all the laundry.

36:23.200 --> 36:30.000
Boy, look at that.
He likes it at Chez Melvin.

36:31.400 --> 36:35.900
What are you coming over here for?
I can't cook with a dog near me.

36:36.100 --> 36:42.500
Just sit. We don't want any company.
I'll read you Emerson.

36:54.100 --> 37:00.000
- How's Verdell doing?
- He's a pain in the ass.

37:03.800 --> 37:10.400
Simon's home. Can you keep the dog
until he's had a chance to adjust?

37:10.600 --> 37:15.200
It's been weeks and weeks.
A few more won't matter.

37:15.400 --> 37:20.900
He wants him back right away.
He'll be by tomorrow.

37:22.700 --> 37:26.500
Okay.

37:32.000 --> 37:35.300
Hungry? Be right with you.

38:38.800 --> 38:40.700
Mr. Udall.

38:46.200 --> 38:50.600
Some face they left hanging on you.
You look like ...

38:50.800 --> 38:54.600
Could you take it ...

38:55.500 --> 38:58.800
... just a little easy, Mr. Udall?

39:02.000 --> 39:04.000
Thank you.

39:06.700 --> 39:09.100
Verdell.

39:10.500 --> 39:14.700
Come here, my beautiful boy.
Come here.

39:14.900 --> 39:18.300
Let's go home and get well.

39:19.400 --> 39:24.400
I can't blame him for being weird.
Look at yourself in the mirror.

39:28.900 --> 39:31.100
Thank you.

39:34.300 --> 39:37.300
Come on, sweetheart.

39:37.500 --> 39:40.800
Verdell, come here.

39:43.000 --> 39:46.000
I know what you want.

39:49.600 --> 39:52.200
Where's my boy?

39:57.600 --> 40:01.400
No, don't force him.

40:33.100 --> 40:37.600
Over a dog!

40:38.200 --> 40:41.800
Over an ugly dog.

40:48.900 --> 40:53.700
Worst sidewalk in New York.
Look where they put it.

41:00.200 --> 41:05.200
- Help!
- You'll make an appointment.

41:05.300 --> 41:09.300
How can you diagnose someone as
an obsessive-compulsive disorder -

41:09.500 --> 41:12.500
- and then act like I had a choice
about barging in?

41:12.700 --> 41:16.100
- You must leave.
- You said you could help me.

41:16.300 --> 41:21.700
- What was that? A tease?
- If you take responsibility ...

41:21.900 --> 41:25.900
- You changed the room around.
- Two years ago.

41:26.100 --> 41:30.100
I also grew a beard, but you're
not interested in changes in me.

41:30.300 --> 41:34.200
I don't have a mountain of time.
I have to get to my restaurant.

41:34.400 --> 41:38.700
Do you know how hard it was for me
to come here?

41:40.100 --> 41:42.500
No, we're not doing this now.

41:42.700 --> 41:47.800
I changed just one pattern,
as you always said I should.

41:48.000 --> 41:50.400
No. Nope.

41:59.600 --> 42:04.400
What if this is
as good as it gets?

42:16.200 --> 42:19.400
What the heck are those for?

42:21.300 --> 42:24.500
No, no, no. Get Carol.

42:24.600 --> 42:30.500
I'm filling in. She might be getting
a job closer to home.

42:32.800 --> 42:37.100
- Why plastic?
- What are you trying to do to me?

42:37.300 --> 42:41.400
- What do you mean?
- Look, elephant girl.

42:41.600 --> 42:47.200
Go get Carol or something.
Just have her do my one meal here.

42:47.400 --> 42:50.400
I'll pay whatever you want.

42:52.800 --> 42:55.100
Do it!

42:57.700 --> 43:01.200
Bryan. Code blue.

43:06.500 --> 43:10.900
Out! Just shut up and get out.

43:11.600 --> 43:17.800
I'll be quiet.
Just let me stay here. No problem.

43:18.000 --> 43:22.300
Go get Carol.

43:22.800 --> 43:28.000
I'm not a prick.
You are. I'm not judging.

43:28.200 --> 43:33.300
This day has been a disaster.

43:34.100 --> 43:37.900
- I'm not sure if I can handle this.
- Get out!

43:38.900 --> 43:45.400
Get out immediately
or there's going to be trouble.

44:00.600 --> 44:02.700
See you.

44:03.800 --> 44:06.100
It's about time.

44:08.000 --> 44:13.500
- Carol's last name?
- Connelly.

44:21.200 --> 44:25.000
- Does he visit often?
- Not really. Not any more.

45:15.500 --> 45:18.300
I'm hungry.

45:18.500 --> 45:21.800
You've ruined my whole day.
I haven't eaten.

45:21.900 --> 45:26.100
- What are you doing here?
- This is not a sexist thing ...

45:26.200 --> 45:29.600
Are you totally gone?
This is my home.

45:31.800 --> 45:37.400
I'm trying to keep emotion aside,
even though it's important.

45:37.600 --> 45:42.600
- I have strong feelings on this.
- What?

45:42.700 --> 45:48.700
That I wasn't there? Do you have
any control over how creepy you get?

45:54.500 --> 45:58.300
Yes, I do.

45:59.100 --> 46:04.900
And to prove it ... I have not
gotten personal, and you have.

46:05.700 --> 46:10.000
Why aren't you at work?
Are you sick?

46:12.100 --> 46:15.500
You don't look sick.

46:16.100 --> 46:19.800
Just tired and bitter.

46:21.800 --> 46:25.000
My son is sick.

46:27.500 --> 46:30.400
What about your mother?

46:30.900 --> 46:36.500
- How do you know about her?
- I hear you talking while I wait.

46:36.600 --> 46:40.700
- Mom, I finished my juice.
- One sec.

46:49.800 --> 46:52.100
How are you doing?

46:57.800 --> 47:00.100
You should answer me.

47:00.300 --> 47:05.100
Sorry, Melvin. I can't handle you
teaching my son manners.

47:08.000 --> 47:10.500
Back to life.

47:18.000 --> 47:20.800
What's wrong?

47:20.900 --> 47:27.200
Five one-thousand,
four one-thousand ...

47:30.000 --> 47:34.000
- 104.9.
- We're going on a cab ride.

47:36.100 --> 47:39.400
Look out, you guys!

47:40.500 --> 47:44.900
Look out.
We're okay. We're okay.

47:46.600 --> 47:49.200
Melvin! Wait!

47:50.200 --> 47:53.200
Melvin! Wait!

47:58.800 --> 48:02.100
Shut up, kids!

48:02.700 --> 48:05.800
Give us a lift, would you?

48:09.900 --> 48:13.300
Cover your mouth when you cough.

48:15.000 --> 48:20.600
- Brooklyn Presbyterian Hospital.
- Hospital?

48:21.100 --> 48:26.400
- Any chance you'll be back today?
- No! Stay away from me.

48:30.900 --> 48:36.700
We can't put this off any longer.
I feel terrible that I have to ...

48:37.100 --> 48:41.500
Could you just leave the dog
for a second?

48:43.300 --> 48:46.100
Sorry.

48:48.900 --> 48:54.000
- What are those cards?
- Frank thought I should have notes.

48:55.000 --> 49:00.000
So I would maintain focus
and not terrify you.

49:00.200 --> 49:05.500
See? He's right.
I need the cards.

49:05.700 --> 49:07.400
SlMON, YOU'RE BROKE

49:14.200 --> 49:19.100
The medical bills are 61,000 now.
And the show didn't go well.

49:19.200 --> 49:24.200
I spoke to your parents.
They didn't hang up or anything.

49:24.400 --> 49:28.300
But they'd feel strange calling you.

49:28.500 --> 49:33.100
I can't call them. Come here, baby.

49:34.300 --> 49:36.300
Come here.

49:36.500 --> 49:40.400
Verdell? What's wrong?

49:40.600 --> 49:45.100
You miss the tough guy?
Well, here I am.

49:45.300 --> 49:50.300
Happy to see me, you little mop?
How about a ride down the chute?

49:50.400 --> 49:53.200
I'm sorry. I didn't mean that.

49:53.300 --> 49:56.100
I didn't mean that, sweetheart.

49:56.200 --> 49:57.900
Sorry ...

49:59.400 --> 50:04.800
I'll be able to keep my apartment
and the studio, won't I?

50:07.400 --> 50:11.400
Oh, my God!

50:41.300 --> 50:45.700
Yes, you make us a lot of money.
But it's more appropriate ...

50:45.800 --> 50:52.700
I need this.
Just say, ''Melvin, I'll try.''

50:55.500 --> 50:59.400
- Melvin, I'll try.
- Thank you.

50:59.600 --> 51:06.000
My son just got accepted to Brown.
My husband was dying.

51:06.100 --> 51:12.000
Good, nice, thrilled, exciting.
You don't have to wait with me.

51:19.800 --> 51:27.300
I can't resist. I just have
so many questions I want to ask you.

51:27.500 --> 51:31.700
You have no idea
what your work means to me.

51:31.900 --> 51:34.500
What does it mean to you?

51:34.800 --> 51:39.400
That somebody out there knows
what it's like to be in here.

51:40.600 --> 51:43.100
God, this is like a nightmare.

51:43.800 --> 51:47.900
Come on.
Just a couple of questions.

51:51.200 --> 51:55.500
- How do you write women so well?
- I think of a man.

51:55.700 --> 52:00.300
And I take away reason
and accountability.

52:31.700 --> 52:34.100
- Mom!
- ln here, Mrs. Connelly.

52:34.300 --> 52:37.500
- Please, what?
- I'm ...

52:37.700 --> 52:40.300
- Tell me!
- Dr. Bettes.

52:40.500 --> 52:45.400
- Not your name. Where is he?
- He's in the bathroom.

52:46.000 --> 52:50.500
What's wrong? You know there are
doctors that come to your house?

52:50.600 --> 52:53.400
I'm home.

52:53.600 --> 52:57.900
I didn't know you had an admirer.
Oh, you met the gift.

52:59.100 --> 53:02.300
He's good. I'm an expert on doctors.

53:02.500 --> 53:05.500
Okay, doctor?

53:05.700 --> 53:09.400
My wife is
Melvin Udall's publisher.

53:09.600 --> 53:14.900
I'm to take care of this little guy
because you are needed at work.

53:15.100 --> 53:19.400
- What kind of work do you do?
- I'm a waitress.

53:19.700 --> 53:23.600
- ln Manhattan.
- Dr. Bettes?

53:23.800 --> 53:26.300
Excuse me.

53:27.800 --> 53:32.100
- I'm sorry it took so long.
- I couldn't find it, either.

53:32.300 --> 53:38.700
Could you get this to the lab?
I want it back today.

53:38.900 --> 53:45.100
- Did you say ''today''?
- Yes. Let's sit down.

53:46.000 --> 53:51.500
These are the receipts from
all the prescriptions for the year.

53:51.700 --> 53:57.400
- The calendar.
- This is a calendar of days.

53:57.500 --> 54:00.700
- And how he felt.
- Good.

54:00.900 --> 54:05.500
- How long has he had the problem?
- Since forever. Six months old.

54:05.700 --> 54:08.400
Have they done blood tests?

54:08.600 --> 54:12.400
- When he was well?
- No.

54:12.500 --> 54:15.800
- And how about skin testing?
- No.

54:16.000 --> 54:19.000
- No standard scratch test?
- No.

54:19.200 --> 54:24.800
They said my plan didn't cover it.
Why? Should they have?

54:26.200 --> 54:29.300
Fucking HMO bastard pieces of shit!

54:31.400 --> 54:35.000
- I'm sorry.
- That's their technical name.

54:37.200 --> 54:43.500
Once the tests come back,
is there someone we should talk to?

54:43.700 --> 54:47.400
Me.
My home number is on the card.

54:48.600 --> 54:51.500
His home number.

54:56.600 --> 54:59.900
- What?
- Your home ...

55:03.600 --> 55:09.200
- Can we get you anything else?
- No, thank you.

55:09.400 --> 55:13.300
Couple of female slaves?

55:13.400 --> 55:18.200
There's still a lot of tests
I need to do.

55:18.400 --> 55:22.200
Whatever I find out,
I promise you, -

55:22.300 --> 55:27.300
- from now on your son is going
to feel a great deal better.

55:35.700 --> 55:38.000
Doc!

55:42.500 --> 55:46.600
That's good.

55:51.900 --> 55:55.900
Let me know about the costs.
One way or another we'll ...

55:56.200 --> 56:00.200
The costs
are going to be considerable.

56:00.400 --> 56:05.300
But Mr. Udall wants to be billed.

56:08.200 --> 56:10.900
That's wonderful.

56:14.200 --> 56:17.700
Thank you for everything, Nora.

56:18.000 --> 56:23.300
Forgive my crankiness. I'll call
when things get back on track.

56:30.800 --> 56:36.300
- What's wrong?
- Who's going to walk Verdell?

56:38.300 --> 56:40.300
No!

56:55.000 --> 56:59.200
- ls he dead yet?
- No.

57:00.000 --> 57:06.200
Would there be any way you would
be willing to walk his dog for him?

57:06.500 --> 57:12.800
- Absolutely.
- You're a wonderful man.

57:14.000 --> 57:20.200
Two o'clock would be a good time.
Here is the key in case he's asleep.

57:21.500 --> 57:26.800
Open his curtains for him
so he can see God's beautiful work.

57:26.900 --> 57:31.900
And he'll know that even things
like this happen for the best.

57:32.100 --> 57:36.700
Did you learn to talk like this in
a ''Sailor, wanna hump-hump''-bar?

57:36.900 --> 57:40.100
Or is this your last shot
at his whisky?

57:40.300 --> 57:44.700
Sell crazy someplace else.
We're all stocked up here.

57:52.800 --> 57:58.700
No! A goofy man is behind this.
You can't block out that man.

57:58.900 --> 58:04.200
Do you really want to go back to
emergency, where they can't help?

58:04.600 --> 58:09.600
This lets a crazy man
into our lives.

58:12.300 --> 58:15.600
You know how this will turn out.

58:15.800 --> 58:20.900
This is not like a string of pearls.
You don't send this one back.

58:25.600 --> 58:27.900
Right?

58:33.000 --> 58:38.000
No. I do, I understand.
Listen. I have to go, okay?

58:38.900 --> 58:42.800
FRlENDS TO ASK FOR MONEY

58:43.500 --> 58:45.600
Bye.

58:46.200 --> 58:48.200
Bye-bye.

58:52.100 --> 58:54.400
What a day ...

58:54.700 --> 58:57.800
Maybe I'll bring him some food by.

58:58.000 --> 59:00.700
Thank you for walking him.

59:02.700 --> 59:08.100
- Excuse me, I'm not feeling well.
- This place smells like shit.

59:08.300 --> 59:10.500
Go away.

59:10.800 --> 59:16.100
- This cleaning lady doesn't ..?
- Please, just leave.

59:17.700 --> 59:22.600
- What happened to your friends?
- Get out of here!

59:28.000 --> 59:31.400
There's nothing worse than having
to feel this way in front of you.

59:32.900 --> 59:37.700
Nellie.
Your a disgrace to depression.

59:38.800 --> 59:44.700
- Rot in hell, Melvin.
- No need to stop being a lady.

59:44.900 --> 59:48.000
You'll be back on your knees
in no time.

59:56.800 --> 01:00:00.000
ls this fun for you?

01:00:00.500 --> 01:00:06.600
It keeps getting better and better.
I'm losing my apartment, Melvin.

01:00:06.700 --> 01:00:11.700
Frank wants me to beg my parents,
who haven't called me, for help.

01:00:12.500 --> 01:00:14.400
And I won't.

01:00:14.600 --> 01:00:17.900
I don't want to paint any more.

01:00:18.200 --> 01:00:21.500
The life I was trying for, is over.

01:00:21.700 --> 01:00:27.500
The life I had is gone
and I'm feeling sorry for myself.

01:00:28.100 --> 01:00:33.500
It's high times for you, isn't it?
The gay neighbour is terrified.

01:00:34.200 --> 01:00:36.600
Terrified!

01:00:48.300 --> 01:00:52.300
I was trying to give you a boost.

01:00:52.400 --> 01:00:57.200
Lucky you.
You're here for rock bottom.

01:00:57.400 --> 01:01:01.700
You absolute horror
of a human being.

01:01:14.400 --> 01:01:19.400
The one thing I'll do for you
might cheer you up.

01:01:19.600 --> 01:01:22.100
Get out.

01:01:22.400 --> 01:01:26.400
You want to know why the dog
prefers me? It's not affection.

01:01:26.600 --> 01:01:29.200
It's a trick.

01:01:31.200 --> 01:01:34.500
I keep bacon in my pocket.

01:01:35.100 --> 01:01:37.300
See?

01:01:43.000 --> 01:01:48.900
We'll both call him. You'll see.
It's a trick.

01:01:57.300 --> 01:02:00.600
Come here, Verdell.

01:02:05.400 --> 01:02:08.000
Come on.

01:02:08.400 --> 01:02:10.400
Come here.

01:02:15.600 --> 01:02:19.500
Just a stupid dog.

01:02:22.700 --> 01:02:26.800
Could you leave now? Please?

01:02:28.900 --> 01:02:32.500
I don't get it.

01:04:08.800 --> 01:04:10.800
Mr. Udall!

01:04:12.600 --> 01:04:16.100
- Carol the waitress?
- Yes.

01:04:25.900 --> 01:04:30.500
The doctors gave me your address.
I'm sorry about the hour.

01:04:36.200 --> 01:04:39.200
If you ...

01:04:41.800 --> 01:04:48.800
- If it's about thanking me ...
- That's not why I'm here.

01:04:49.000 --> 01:04:54.200
Though it's nice to talk to
a real doctor about Spencer.

01:04:56.900 --> 01:05:01.000
Note. Put it in a note.

01:05:09.600 --> 01:05:15.000
- I have a hairdryer.
- Why did you do this for me?

01:05:19.200 --> 01:05:24.400
- So you'd come back to work.
- That sounds strange.

01:05:27.700 --> 01:05:31.300
I'm worried you did this ...

01:05:46.400 --> 01:05:51.400
Are you waiting for me
to say something?

01:05:53.700 --> 01:05:56.300
Look ...

01:05:58.000 --> 01:06:03.500
- I'll be there tomorrow.
- I need to clear this up now.

01:06:05.000 --> 01:06:07.800
Clear what up?

01:06:09.100 --> 01:06:14.400
I'm not going to sleep with you.
I will never sleep with you.

01:06:15.900 --> 01:06:17.900
Not ever!

01:06:22.400 --> 01:06:26.800
I'm sorry, but ...

01:06:28.700 --> 01:06:34.200
... we don't open
for the no-sex oaths until 9 a.m.

01:06:35.100 --> 01:06:41.200
- I'm not kidding.
- Anything else?

01:06:42.800 --> 01:06:47.700
Just ... thank you.

01:06:53.100 --> 01:06:56.300
So you will be at work tomorrow?

01:06:58.800 --> 01:07:01.300
Yes.

01:07:16.000 --> 01:07:19.500
''Never'', she said.

01:07:37.400 --> 01:07:41.300
I took a chance you were up.

01:07:41.600 --> 01:07:44.900
I brought you some Chinese soup.

01:07:47.200 --> 01:07:49.300
Thanks.

01:08:05.800 --> 01:08:09.500
I've never been this tired
in my life.

01:08:16.300 --> 01:08:19.800
I haven't been sleeping.

01:08:21.100 --> 01:08:26.399
I haven't been clear in my head
or felt like myself.

01:08:29.300 --> 01:08:31.899
I'm in trouble.

01:08:32.399 --> 01:08:35.200
It's not just the tiredness.

01:08:35.700 --> 01:08:40.899
- Sick. Nauseous.
- Sleepy.

01:08:41.100 --> 01:08:47.300
Everything looks distorted
and everything inside aches.

01:08:47.500 --> 01:08:51.300
You can barely find the will
to complain.

01:08:55.399 --> 01:08:59.000
I'm glad we did this.

01:08:59.700 --> 01:09:02.899
Good talking to you.

01:09:10.600 --> 01:09:16.899
- Still writing that thank-you note?
- How do you spell ''conscience''?

01:09:17.100 --> 01:09:20.500
C-O-N-S-C-I-E-N-C-E.

01:09:20.600 --> 01:09:25.899
Look, I got Sean to babysit
so we could go out.

01:09:26.000 --> 01:09:29.899
I don't feel safe
leaving Spencer with someone.

01:09:30.000 --> 01:09:35.200
Spencer's okay. Start finding
something to do with your free time.

01:09:36.399 --> 01:09:39.800
Sean, are you hungry?

01:09:40.800 --> 01:09:47.100
We got pizza. Sausage, pepperoni.
You want to make this later?

01:09:48.800 --> 01:09:52.399
We are going out, like people do.

01:09:54.400 --> 01:10:00.700
